'''''Star Wars Insider'' 46''' is the forty-sixth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[October]] [[1999]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]: Michael Sheard" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: [[Paul Martin Smith]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*"[[Bookshelf|''Star Wars'' Bookshelf]]" &ndash; Prime Time: R.A. Salvatore and the New Jedi Order {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; What to Do With a Creased Poster Besides Cry {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[A Jedi Trio]]" {{C|by [[Kevin Fitzpatrick]]}}
*:<small>[[Liam Neeson]], [[Samuel L. Jackson]], and [[Jake Lloyd]] sat down for brief Q&A sessions with the ''Insider'' right after they first saw [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']]. Find out how the Jedi judge the final product—and discover their new hopes for [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|Episode II]].</small>
*"[[Return of the Ewok (article)|''Return of the Ewok'']]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Never-before-published photos! Take a look at the "home movie mockumentary" made by ''[[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|Return of the Jedi]]''{{'s}} assistant director during the [[1982]] filming of ''Jedi'' that stars [[Warwick Davis]], along with hilarious cameos from [[Mark Hamill]], [[Harrison Ford]], [[Carrie Fisher]], and more!</small>
*"[[The Art of Episode I]]"
*:<small>Beautiful reproductions of the concept art that showed the look of ''The Phantom Menace'' are showcased in this exclusive excerpt from ''The Art of Episode I''. From early [[Podracer/Legends|Podracers]] to the intriguing [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] Witch, you won't believe your eyes!</small>
*"[[The Vehicles of Episode I]]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Master, what's a [[bongo]]? It's a [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] sub, of course, and it's just one of a new fleet of speeders, ships, and tanks that power the forces of good and evil in the first episode of the ''Star Wars'' saga. A revealing, in-depth overview from [[David West Reynolds]], author of ''[[Star Wars: Episode I The Visual Dictionary]]''.</small>
*"[[Anthony Daniels: Nuts and Bolts]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>After four movies, two cartoons, innumerable commercials, and one "[[The Star Wars Holiday Special|Holiday Special]]" as the beloved [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], Anthony Daniels is still going strong as one of the biggest stars in the ''Star Wars'' universe. The author of the ''Insider''{{'s}} Wonder Column tells [[Scott Chernoff]] what the part means to him, and where he hopes to take it in the future.</small>

